  "market_context": "Price had broken two successive demand zones in a bearish single-leg move, creating a new supply zone at the extreme. After a pullback, it formed a double top (equal highs) above a decisional supply zone, indicating unresolved liquidity above.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst emphasized that traders must wait for a liquidity sweep of the upper supply zone (above the double tops) before entering short trades, as entering at the decisional zone risks being stopped out by the sweep.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price broke two successive demand zones in a bearish single-leg move, forming a new HTF supply zone at the extreme.",
    "Step 2: Observe the subsequent pullback that failed to mitigate the extreme supply zone and instead formed a double top (equal highs) with liquidity pools marked by '$' symbols.",
    "Step 3: Recognize the lower supply zone as the 'decisional zone' and the upper one as the 'extreme zone', warning against entering at the decisional zone.",
    "Step 4: Conclude that price is likely to sweep the upper liquidity (above double tops) to trigger stop-losses before continuing downward, making the sweep a required confirmation for short entries."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Never enter at a decisional zone when an extreme zone with accumulated liquidity exists above; always wait for the liquidity sweep to confirm institutional intent and avoid being trapped as liquidity.",
